# Git Commands Practice


git init
git status
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git branch feature-login
git checkout feature-login
git merge feature-login
git push origin main
git pull origin main


1.git init  
Initializes a new Git repository in your project folder.  
Used when starting version control for a new project.

2.git status  
Shows the current state of files in your repository.  
Displays modified, staged, and untracked files.

3.git add .  
Stages all changed files for the next commit.  
Used before committing changes to Git history.

4.git commit -m "message"  
Creates a saved snapshot of your staged changes.  
The message describes what changes were made.

